detaileddescription.para:
Then memory allocated for this object is freed and the object is removed from a device 
calls co_dev_remove_obj(), which removes the object from the device 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_obj_clear()

Then 0 is returned and the sub-object is removed from the object 
calls rbtree_remove() 
calls rbnode_init() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_fini() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_obj_update()

Then a pointer to the sub-object (co_sub_t) is returned, the sub-object is initialized with the requested sub-index, type, value null pointer and all other default values 
calls rbnode_init() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_init_min() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_init_max() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_DEFAULT: calls co_val_init()

Then a pointer to the sub-object is returned, sub-object lower and upper limits are set to default values 
calls rbnode_init() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_init_min() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_init_max() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_DEFAULT: calls co_val_init()

Then a pointer to sub-object (co_sub_t) is returned, the default upload indicator is set 
calls rbnode_init() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_init_min() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_init_max() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_DEFAULT: calls co_val_init()

Then the sub-object is finalized and removed from the object 
calls co_obj_remove_sub() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_DEFAULT: calls co_val_fini() 
if !LELY_NO_CO_OBJ_LIMITS: calls co_val_fini()

Then -1 is returned, nothing is changed 
calls co_sub_get_type() 
if LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_type_is_array() 
calls co_sdo_req_dn_val() 
calls co_sub_chk_val() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_fini()

Then -1 is returned, the abort code is set to what is returned from a call to co_sub_chk_val() with the data type of the sub-object and the value from the request, nothing is changed 
calls co_sub_get_type() 
if LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_type_is_array() 
calls co_sdo_req_dn_val() 
calls co_sub_chk_val() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_fini()

Then 0 is returned, the abort code is not changed, the value from the request is downloaded to the sub-object 
calls co_sub_get_type() 
if LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_type_is_array() 
if LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_init_array() 
calls co_sdo_req_dn_val() 
calls co_sub_chk_val() 
calls co_sub_dn() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_fini()

Then 0 is returned, the requested value is downloaded to the sub-object 
if LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_copy() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_fini() 
if !LELY_NO_MALLOC: calls co_val_move()
